{"lemma":"صَدَماتٌ","slug":"صَدَماتٌ","root":"ص.د.م","root_slug":"ص-د-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-د-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24032","n24036","n24037"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shock"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clash, stroke"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calamity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"baldness of the temples","examples":[{"text":"صَدْمَتَان","english":"the temples"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun of صَدَمَ (ṣadama, “to strike, shock”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24032","headword_ar":"صَدَمَهُ","root":"Sdm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadomN","text_ar":"صَدْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dashed himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, TA,) i. e., a thing: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he struck it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knocked it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knocked against it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] namely, a hard thing with the like thereof. (M, K.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobu A_i*aA qatala AlS~ayoda SadomFA laA yuw^okalu","text_ar":"الكَلْبُ اـِذَا قَتَلَ الصَّيْدَ صَدْمًا لَا يُوْكَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the dog kills the game by dashing himself against it, it shall not be eaten"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) [See also 3.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadamahu","text_ar":"صَدَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, (Msb,) and so the inf. n., (Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pushed, thrust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repelled, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadamotu Al$~ar~a biAl$~ar~i","text_ar":"صَدَمْتُ الشَّرَّ بِالشَّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I repelled evil with evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadamatohu Humay~aA AlkaA^osi","text_ar":"صَدَمَتْهُ حُمَيَّا الكَاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The intoxicating influence of the cup of wine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smote him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attacked him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadamahumo A^amorN","text_ar":"صَدَمَهُمْ اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) inf. n. as above, (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An event befell them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, * TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadamahu biAlqawoli","text_ar":"صَدَمَهُ بِالقَوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He silenced him by speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Mgh","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n24036","headword_ar":"صَدْمَةٌ","root":"Sdm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single shock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collision:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single impulsion, push,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vehement befalling of an event."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aboru Einoda AlS~adomapi AlA^uwlaY","text_ar":"الصَّبْرُ عِنْدَ الصَّدْمَةِ الاُولَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA) i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Patience is"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be exercised]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the first"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the calamity: (TA:) meaning that patience is the last thing in the case of every misfortune, (S, Msb,) but it is [most] commended, (S,) or is most rewarded, (Msb,) on the occasion of the sharpness, or vehemence, thereof. (S, Msb.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotu","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^amorayoni SadomapF waAHidapF","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَمْرَيْنِ صَدْمَةً وَاحِدَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made an end of the two affairs at one dash,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at one stroke"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A baldness in the side of the forehead;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazoEapN","text_ar":"نَزْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~adimataAni","text_ar":"الصَّدِمَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["KL","TA","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n24037","headword_ar":"صِدْمَةٌ","root":"Sdm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SidomN","text_ar":"صِدْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}